An Animal Incursion Detection System (aIDS) is a system that monitors activities and issues alert when a suspicious activity is discovered in a farm or village.

Where are we going to use it?

1>Farmers have to watch their crops to protect them from animals which destroy them.
2>They either hire someone to watch it or do it themselves.
3>It will help them to reduce human efforts.
4>It will help them increase the production.
5>It will increase their income.
